-- ACWA Holding Bids for Saudi Cooling Project Contracts Worth $450 Million
-- B y   A y e s h a   D a y a
-- 2010-09-27T09:08:46Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-09-27/acwa-holding-bids-for-saudi-cooling-project-contracts-worth-450-million.html
ACWA Holding, a Saudi-based power
and water company, is bidding for 1.7 billion riyals ($450
million) of district cooling projects, the chief executive
officer said in Abu Dhabi today.  The four projects are the Jeddah corniche, a knowledge city
in Medina, a petrochemicals plant in Jubail and a venture in
Mecca, Rasheed al-Rasheed told reporters at the Middle East
Economic Digest Middle East District Cooling 2010 conference.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ayesha Daya in Dubai at 
